          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The isomeric  ratios  in  the reactions (gamma,n) and",
                " (n,2n) leading to the production of odd-odd nuclides",
                " 184Re, 190Ir, and 196Au  presented. The measurements",
                " were performed   by   activation   method   at   the",
                " irradiation of  natural  Re,  Ir,  and Au samples by",
                " 14.7 MeV  neutrons  and  by  Bremsstrahlung  with  a",
                " end-point energy  of  22 MeV.  Identification of the",
                " obtained nuclei in isomeric and  ground  states  was",
                " made basing on their spectra of X or g radiation and",
                " the half-life.  A calculation of isomeric ratios was",
                " performed on the basis of statistical model, and the",
                " parameters describing the dependence  of  the  level",
                " density on   the   excitation   energy  and  angular",
                " momentum were  determined  from  the  comparison  of",
                " experimental and calculated values. The influence of",
                " the nuclear  structure  on   these   parameters   is",
                " discussed."
              ]
            }
          ],
